ction merrill lynch expanded capital markets and fueled the growth of the american economy after world war ii catching lightning in a bottle is the first complete history of merrill lynch and traces its impact on the world of finance from the day charlie merrill opened his oneman shop in  to the final shareholder meeting prior to its acquisition by bank of america in the book sheds vital light on two eras the early years that saw the expansion of the firm and of populist finance and on the bleakpostmillennial decade when its confidence and vision collapsed along with much of wall streets reputation as mr smiths book shows merrills success had broad implications sadly so did its travails the economista wonderful story of creativity and entrepreneurship a terrific read consuelo mack wealthtrack an accurate story of the rise and fall of americas preeminent brokerage firm no novel could be as captivating no characters as rich and fascinating as those who fill the pages of this remarkable book arthur levitt former chairman sechttpsmithmerrillhistorycomauthors winthrop h smith jrsummarywinthrop h smith jr also known as win is the son and namesake of a founder of merrill lynch in  win came to work for the company his late father had coled starting as an entrylevel associate he rose steadily working in not only investment banking but also marketing human resources finance and sales he held management positions in the capital markets group and private client group during the final decade of his twentyeightyear career win was an executive vice president of merrill lynch  co and a member of the executive committee as chairman of merrill lynch international he led one of merrill lynch  co’s four business units with  employees over b in revenues and client assets of b known as a charismatic leader and strategic thinker win built lasting relationships with corporate executives and highnetworth individuals worldwidewin smith chose to end his successful wall street career and retired from merrill in january  because he could not agree with the future direction of the firm invited to the podium at the final merrill lynch shareholders meeting in  he delivered a speech that was to have profound impact throughout the worldin  win published the first complete history of merrill lynch catching lightning in a bottle how merrill lynch revolutionized the financial world the book sold over  copies the first year and received highprofile media attention httpwwwsmithmerrillhistorycomtoday win enjoys a second career as president of sugarbush resort in warren vt he is also chairman and ceo of summit ventures ne llc which owns sugarbush httpswwwsugarbushcommr smith is vicechair of the national ski areas association a director of the vermont ski areas association lead director of agf management limited and a director of eaton vance corporation former directorships include united nations association cri outward bound japan society and deerfield academyorganizationsagf management limitedlead directorstarting eaton vance corporationindependent directorstarting national ski areas associationvicechairvermont business roundtablechairvermont ski areas associationmember of the board of directorsrichardson gmp limitedchairman of the boardstarting richardson financial group limitedindependent directorstarting educationamherst collegebachelor of arts political sciencebachelor of arts political science – activities and societies chi psi varsity soccer rugbydeerfield academy – buckley school – skillsleadershipcorporate governancebusiness ethicsstrategic planninginvestmentsmarketing strategywealth managementmanagementteam buildingentrepreneurshipsecuritiespublic speakingbusiness developmentskinonprofitssee asset managmentventure capitalnonprofitsbudgetssmall businesshigh net worth individualswall streetmerrill lynchfinancial analysisorganizational developmentcustomer servicesee lesshows this translationgreat•has errorsthanks for your helpview winthrop h’s full profile tos