or charles e merrill  co was founded smith who began as a junior runner and clerk at merrill was groomed by founder charles e merrill who also was an amherst alumnus smiths career would span more than four decades as he would ultimately serve as directing partner of the firm in  and  smith was an architect of merills transformative mergers including ea pierce  co and cassatt  co in  followed by the acquisition of fenner  beane in  smith is often credited with having implemented charles e merrills strategy of bringing wall street to main street and received both respect and affection from his colleagues in the industry and at his firm in  smith handed over daytoday control of the firm at the time known as merrill lynch pierce fenner  beane in recognition of his role in building merrill into a leading national brokerage smiths name was added to that of the firm becoming merrill lynch pierce fenner  smith smiths name replaced that of alpheus beanes who firm fenner  beane had merged with merrill in  smith is the father of winthrop h smith jr a former merrill lynch executive he died on january   in litchfield connecticut referencesedit  a b c d wall street s for b time magazine jan    qa win smith sugarbush resort vermont business magazine mar    coleaders the power of great partnerships john wiley and sons   winthrop smith broker  dead new york times january   retrieved   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlewinthrophsmitholdid categories merrill lynch peopleamerican financial businesspeopleamerican stockbrokers births deathsamherst college alumniphillips academy alumnipeople from hadley massachusettshidden categories pages to import images to wikidataarticles with hcards navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikiped